===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The portion of a hammer containing the metal striking face (also including the [[claw]] or [[peen]] if so equipped).
# {{lb|en|zoology}} Any of various [[shark]]s of the genera ''[[Sphyrna]]'' or ''[[Zygaena]]'' having the eyes set on projections from the sides of the head, which gives it a hammer shape.
# {{lb|en|zoology}} A fresh-water fish; the [[hogsucker]], {{taxlink|Hypentelium nigricans|species}}, in the [[sucker]] family [[Catostomidae]].
# {{lb|en|zoology}} An African fruit bat, the {{vern|hammer-headed fruit bat}}, {{taxlink|Hypsignathus monstrosus|species|noshow=1}}, so called from its large blunt nozzle.
# {{lb|en|slang}} A stupid person, a [[dunce]].
#* '''1960''', {{w|P. G. Wodehouse}}, ''{{w|Jeeves in the Offing}}'', chapter V:
#*: [The butler] joined us with a telegram for Bobbie on a salver. From her mother, I presumed, calling me some name which she had forgotten to insert in previous communications. Or, of course, possibly expressing once more her conviction that I was a guffin, which, I thought, having had time to ponder over it, would be something in the nature of a bohunkus or a '''hammerhead'''.
#  A turn-around; a parking area constructed in a subdivision for initial access and construction.
# {{lb|en|biology}} A kind of [[ribozyme]]; [[hammerhead ribozyme]].
